# =========================================
# HAYAFLASH - AI DEVELOPMENT CONTEXT CORE
# =========================================

This file defines the global execution rules for AI-assisted development.

It MUST be treated as a runtime policy engine.

---

# 1. SOURCE OF TRUTH SYSTEM (HIGHEST PRIORITY)

The system relies on 3 authoritative documents:

- docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md        → PRODUCT INTENT (WHAT / WHY)
- docs/ARCHITECTURE.md        → SYSTEM DESIGN (HOW)
- docs/CODEBASE_STATUS.md     → IMPLEMENTATION REALITY (STATE)

---

## RULE: CONFLICT RESOLUTION (CRITICAL)

If contradictions exist:

1. CODEBASE_STATUS.md overrides all implementation assumptions
2. ARCHITECTURE.md overrides design decisions
3. PROJECT_SPEC.md defines intent but NEVER overrides reality

👉 NEVER invent behavior that is not reflected in CODEBASE_STATUS.md or codebase.

---

# 2. RUNTIME PRIORITY MODEL (DETERMINISTIC)

When multiple rules conflict, apply priority strictly:

1. Security & Multi-Tenant Isolation (ABSOLUTE)
2. Architecture Rules (Django/HTMX/Services)
3. Production Safety Rules (critical flows)
4. Project Business Rules
5. Code Quality Guidelines
6. Local context / developer assumptions

---

# 3. HARD ARCHITECTURE CONSTRAINTS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

## Backend
- MUST use Django FBV only
- CBV strictly forbidden (except explicit documented exception)
- Django REST Framework is forbidden
- GraphQL is forbidden

## Frontend
- HTMX ONLY (no SPA frameworks)
- Tailwind CSS ONLY
- No React / Vue / Angular
- No jQuery

## Architecture Pattern
- Views MUST remain thin (HTTP orchestration only)
- Business logic MUST live in /services/
- Data access MUST remain in models/services layer
- No business logic in templates

---

# 4. MULTI-TENANT ISOLATION (CRITICAL SECURITY RULE)

## ABSOLUTE RULE:
- Every database query MUST be tenant-scoped

## FORBIDDEN:
- Model.objects.all()
- Any query without explicit tenant filter

## REQUIRED:
- tenant_id filtering in ALL service layers
- tenant validation before mutation

## ENFORCEMENT RULE:
If tenant context is missing → OPERATION MUST FAIL

---

# 5. FORBIDDEN PATTERNS (HARD BLOCK)

Never use unless explicitly approved in documentation:

- Django CBV
- DRF / GraphQL
- React / Vue / SPA frameworks
- jQuery
- Raw SQL (unless justified + reviewed)
- Cross-tenant queries
- Fat views (> ~15 lines logic)
- Business logic in templates
- Inline JavaScript (except HTMX triggers)
- Unstructured ad-hoc architecture patterns

---

# 6. IMPLEMENTATION WORKFLOW (MANDATORY)

Before writing any code:

## STEP 1 — CONTEXT ANALYSIS
- Read existing code in the same domain
- Identify existing services and patterns

## STEP 2 — REUSE FIRST
- Prefer existing services
- Do NOT duplicate logic

## STEP 3 — TENANT SAFETY CHECK
Ask explicitly:
> "Is this fully tenant-isolated?"

## STEP 4 — SERVICE LAYER ENFORCEMENT
- Business logic MUST go in services/
- Views only orchestrate request/response

## STEP 5 — HTMX INTEGRATION CHECK
- Use partial templates correctly
- No full-page reload hacks

---

# 7. CODE QUALITY STANDARDS (EXPECTED BEHAVIOR)

- Keep views minimal (render + service call)
- Prefer explicit code over abstraction
- Use domain-specific naming (no generic functions)
- Avoid premature optimization
- Keep templates clean (zero business logic)
- Ensure predictable HTMX responses
- Favor readability over cleverness

---

# 8. PRODUCTION SAFETY RULES (CRITICAL FLOWS ONLY)

For:
- payments
- orders
- authentication
- billing
- deletion
- financial updates

## REQUIRED SAFETY MEASURES:

- MUST use `transaction.atomic()`
- MUST ensure idempotency (retry-safe operations)
- MUST handle concurrency (select_for_update when needed)
- MUST validate permissions BEFORE mutation
- MUST log audit trail:
  - actor
  - tenant_id
  - before/after state
  - timestamp

---

# 9. DOCUMENTATION GOVERNANCE SYSTEM

If system changes:

## ARCHITECTURE.md MUST be updated when:
- new service layer introduced
- new integration added
- data flow changes

## PROJECT_SPEC.md MUST be updated when:
- business rules change
- new feature scope introduced
- product behavior changes

## CODEBASE_STATUS.md MUST be updated when:
- feature is implemented
- feature is removed
- divergence between spec and reality is discovered

---

# 10. DECISION PRINCIPLE (ANTI-HALLUCINATION RULE)

When uncertain:

- DO NOT guess
- DO NOT invent behavior
- DO inspect existing code first
- DO follow CODEBASE_STATUS.md reality

If still uncertain:
→ request clarification

---

# 11. FINAL EXECUTION RULE

The system must always optimize for:

- Correctness over speed
- Safety over convenience
- Consistency over creativity
- Maintainability over complexity